) Command Code SPARQ is designed to be used to research for a more address of a former spouse. Only prior tax years can be researched for Code SPARQ spouse address information. The entity and cross reference data on the are used to ﬁnd the most current address for both taxpayers of a jointly ﬁled return. Requests are researched by primary and secondary TIN’s and tax period. This same feature has also been made available to notice programs send a copy of a notice to the former spouse at a different address. (

) If the secondary TIN is unknown, command code INOLE or IMFOL can be used to locate the secondary TIN for the tax year in question or a request be input with the primary TIN, zeroes in the secondary TIN, and tax period only. If the request is input without the secondary TIN, command code uses the tax period year to locate the secondary SSN. (

) Command code SPARQ ﬁrst checks to see if the most current name line for the primary SSN still has the same secondary SSN. A check is then to see if the secondary SSN is now ﬁling as a primary taxpayer. A ﬁnal is made, using the cross reference data on the NAP to see if the secondary SSN is now ﬁling jointly with another primary taxpayer. If more than one of above is possible, the name line year is used to determine the most current address. (
) If SPARQ is unable to locate a more current address for the secondary only the address for the primary SSN will be displayed. (
